1) Semicolon : The easiest way to chain a command is ; in most context ; seperate commands in a similar way to how to enter seperate lines
echo "hello" > linux ; cat linux

2) && : The && operator allows you to run a second command only if first command is succeed.
  command1 && command2
it means run command1 and if it succeed , then run command2

3) || : this operator allows you to run a command only if first command fails.
  command1 || command2
 it means run command1 and if it fails run commmand2

